cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on the application of deep learning models for the classification and localization of diseases in histology images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of weakly-supervised learning methods also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges related to the nature and availability of labeled histology images, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
